<div class="body">

<p style="font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;">NTP</p>

<p>NTP version 4, a significant revision of the previous NTP standard, is the current development version. It is formalized by the following documents:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc5905.txt">RFC 5905: Network Time Protocol Version 4: Protocol and Algorithms Specification</a></li> 
<li><a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc5906.txt">RFC 5906: Network Time Protocol Version 4: Autokey Specification</a></li> 
<li><a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc5907.txt">RFC 5907: Definitions of Managed Objects for Network Time Protocol Version 4 (NTPv4)</a></li> 
<li><a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc5908.txt">RFC 5908: Network Time Protocol (NTP) Server Option for DHCPv6</a></li> 
</ul>

<p style="font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;">SNTP</p>

<p>Simple NTP (SNTP) version 4 is described in
<a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc5905.txt">RFC 5905</a>.
</p>

</div>
